<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORE AFTERSHOCKS RATTLE WESTSIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two earthquakes shook the Westside and other parts of Los Angeles County 
shortly before midnight Monday, Caltech reported. 
</P>
<P>
 At 11:49 p.m. Sunday, a 3.6-magnitude quake struck three miles southeast of 
Simi Valley, seismologist Jim Mori said. It was followed at 11:50 p.m. by a 
3.7-magnitude temblor in the same location. Both were aftershocks from the Jan. 
17 Northridge quake, Mori said. 
</P>
<P>
 There were no reports of injuries or damages, but the jolts were felt strongly 
across the Westside. 
</P>
</TEXT>
