<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; TRANSPORTATION: FREE SHUTTLES IN SANTA MONICA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Shuttle buses are offering free rides between the Santa Monica business 
district and the MGM Plaza/Water Gardens area and between downtown and the Main 
Street restaurant and shopping district. 
</P>
<P>
 Designed to reduce the hassle of traffic and parking for lunchtime strollers 
and diners, the east-west line of the Tide Shuttle will serve 10 stops at 
20-minute intervals from 11 a.m. to 3 p.m. every weekday. 
</P>
<P>
 Its electric-powered line will extend from 26th Street to Ocean Avenue along 
Colorado Avenue and Broadway. 
</P>
<P>
 The service's two-month trial run, which began Monday, is being sponsored by 
the city, the Central Business District and Southern California Edison. 
</P>
<P>
 An additional service funded by the city and Santa Monica Place will connect 
the shopping center with the Main Street area at 15-minute intervals daily from 
noon to 10 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Information on shuttle stops and times: (310) 393-9825. 
</P>
