<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94: SEMIFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; SHINING THROUGH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WILLIAM TUOHY, Times London Bureau 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Several British tabloids have noticed the hair -- or lack of it -- on the 
heads of Bulgarian players. 
</P>
<P>
 Borislav Mihaylov, the goalkeeper and captain, spent $20,000 on a Paris hair 
transplant while playing for Mulhouse in the French Second Division, they 
report. Mihaylov is said to have his personal hairdresser, Romain Steffan, in 
the United States. 
</P>
<P>
 Other commentators pointed to the dramatic header by Yordan Lechkov against 
Germany and suggested that Lechkov's baldness may have contributed to his 
effectiveness in making the goal that beat Germany. He had no hair to get 
between his skull and the soccer ball, they noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
