<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94: SEMIFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; ANOTHER WORLD CUP AMERICANIZATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RANDY HARVEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As channel surfing foreigners here for the World Cup discovered Tuesday night, 
a sport is not considered legitimate unless it has an all-star team. 
</P>
<P>
 So, for the first time, the international soccer federation, FIFA will 
announce an 11-man all-star team from the 1994 World Cup on Friday at the 
Ritz-Carlton Huntington in Pasadena. 
</P>
<P>
 Two of the finalists being considered by FIFA's Technical Study Group include 
the United States' Tab Ramos and Alexi Lalas. RANDY HARVEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
