<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94: SEMIFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; THE ENEMY IS US 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By VILLAS-BOAS CORREA, Jornal do Brasil 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Our worst adversary . . . is not Sweden or Bulgaria or Italy. . . . The 
Brazilian team can only lose to itself. Knock on wood . . . the team will only 
lose if we fall into the trap of arrogance, of self-confidence that 
underestimates our opponents . . . for 1938, 1950 and 1982 (World Cup years in 
which Brazil was highly ranked) taught even the hardest heads that being a 
favorite doesn't win a game. 
</P>
