<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94: SEMIFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; A COSTLY DEFEAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WILLIAM TUOHY, Times London Bureau 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Financial Times of London reported that Germany's loss to Bulgaria cost 
the German players bonuses of $80,000 apiece for defending their title.For 
reaching the quarterfinals, they received a mere $22,000 per man. 
</P>
<P>
 The paper noted that Romania's players are to be made Citizens of Honor of 
Bucharest for their World Cup performance, after bowing out in penalty kicks 
against Sweden. 
</P>
<P>
 The only exception is Ion Vladiou, who became a "national shame" when 
suspended for earning the team's only red card. 
</P>
<P>
 Each Romanian player was given a Mercedes by a local businessman. 
</P>
