TEAM USA BEATS LAKERS, 110-99 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Loe Roe of Massachusetts scored 23 points to lead Team USA to a 110-99 victory 
over the Lakers in the ASICS Summer Pro League Wednesday night at the Bren 
Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Arizona's Damon Stoudamire scored 20 points, Michigan State's Shawn Respert 
added 16, Wake Forest's Tim Duncan had 13 and Duke's Cherokee Parks, a Marina 
High graduate, scored 12 for Team USA, which will represent the United States 
at the Goodwill Games in St. Petersburg, Russia, this month. 
</P>
<P>
 Anthony Peeler scored 31 points and Trevor Ruffin 22 for the Lakers, who were 
outscored by 10 in the fourth quarter. 
