<HEADLINE>
<P>
AMERICAN LEGION BASEBALL ROUNDUP; WEISS PITCHES NO-HITTER FOR VAN NUYS SOUTH ON 
TWO DAYS' REST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mike Weiss threw a no-hitter and struck out 11 as Van Nuys South defeated 
Burbank North, 11-0, in an American Legion District 20 game at Burbank High on 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Weiss (3-1), pitching with two days of rest, did not walk a batter in the 
six-inning game that was called because of the 10-run rule. 
</P>
<P>
 Two Burbank North batters reached base when the Van Nuys South catcher 
overthrew first base after dropping third strikes. 
</P>
<P>
 Marc Scorza, Greg Levine and Aaron Amitin led a Van Nuys South offense that 
racked up 15 hits. 
</P>
<P>
 Scorza was four for four, drove in two runs and scored twice. 
</P>
<P>
 Greg Levine was three for three with two runs batted in and two runs, and 
Amitin had a triple, home run and two RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
 In other District 20 games: 
</P>
<P>
 Encino 5, Granada Hills East 4 -- Brian Luderer's infield single scored Jesse 
Slade with the winning run in the bottom of seventh at Valley College. 
</P>
<P>
 Encino (15-3) strung together four consecutive hits with one out in the 
decisive inning to win its third game in a row. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Hebert (4-1) scattered eight hits, gave up four runs -- two earned -- 
struck out three and walked two for Encino. His scoreless-inning streak ended 
at 24 when Granada Hills East scored twice in the sixth. 
</P>
<P>
 Verdugo Hills 11, North Hollywood 8 -- Phil Onsaga was three for three with 
two home runs and pitched five innings to pick up the victory for Verdugo Hills 
(14-5) at Franklin Field in Van Nuys. 
</P>
<P>
 Loren Geller added a home run and two RBIs for Verdugo Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys East 2, Sun Valley 2 -- The top two teams in the Eastern Division 
played eight innings before the umpires called the game at Notre Dame High 
because of darkness. 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys East's Joey Orlando tied the game with a two-run single in the fifth. 
</P>
<P>
 Canoga Park 10, San Fernando 7 -- Sean Hansen broke a 6-6 tie with a two-run 
double, giving Canoga Park (10-8) the victory at San Fernando High. 
</P>
<P>
 Hansen has driven in the go-ahead runs in the last two Canoga Park victories. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeremiah Johnson had five singles in five at-bats with two RBIs for Canoga 
Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodland Hills West 8, West Hills 7 -- Billy Burnette had three hits and Greg 
Kmet pitched his third complete game, leading Woodland Hills West (14-5) at El 
Camino Real High. 
</P>
<P>
 Kmet (4-1), a right-hander, gave up four earned runs in seven innings. He 
struck out three and walked three. 
</P>
<P>
 Las Virgenes 5, Granada Hills West 3 -- Bhret Haessig was three for three and 
drove in the go-ahead runs in the sixth inning with a two-run double, leading 
Las Virgenes (10-8) at Granada Hills High. 
</P>
<P>
 Pat Costello (2-0) picked up the victory in relief and Tyler Taylor finished 
the game, earning his first save. 
</P>
</TEXT>
