<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: HERMOSA BEACH; COUNCIL TABLES VOTE ON ANTI-DRILLING INITIATIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES BENNING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council this week postponed a vote until Aug. 9 on whether to put an 
anti-oil drilling initiative on the statewide November ballot or hold a special 
election next year. 
</P>
<P>
 The initiative's proponents, who collected 1,628 signatures, hope to quash a 
plan by MacPherson Oil Co. of Santa Monica to dig 30 wells at a slant under the 
city. 
</P>
<P>
 Council members said they want to study how a public vote will affect the 
project before they decide whether to place the initiative on the November 
ballot. 
</P>
<P>
 After Hermosa voters approved two pro-oil initiatives in 1984, the oil company 
was granted a lease from the city to drill the wells in a city yard at 6th 
Street and Valley Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Critics say the project poses safety hazards, and contend that voters then 
were swayed by high gasoline prices. But Donald MacPherson Jr., president of 
the oil company, said a vote either way will not affect the project. JAMES 
BENNING 
</P>
</TEXT>
