<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: EL SEGUNDO; ALLIEDSIGNAL IS CITED FOR CHEMICAL LEAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES BENNING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AlliedSignal Inc. was cited by air quality officials for a hydrofluoric acid 
leak June 15 that forced the closure of two streets and the evacuation of a 
golf course and a construction site. 
</P>
<P>
 The company violated two South Coast Air Quality Management District rules by 
creating a public nuisance and failing to operate its equipment according to 
its permit, said AQMD spokesman Sam Atwood. 
</P>
<P>
 Nobody was injured by the leak, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Company officials said about 85 pounds of the chemical leaked from faulty 
lining connecting two pipes in the plant on Sepulveda Boulevard, where 
hydrochlorofluorocarbons are manufactured. 
</P>
<P>
 The company could be fined, and AQMD officials will decide in several weeks 
whether to refer the case to the district attorney's office for criminal 
prosecution. JAMES BENNING 
</P>
</TEXT>
