<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: WILMINGTON; FREE CHILD VACCINATIONS, LEAD TESTING AVAILABLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Free vaccinations and lead testing for children will be offered in Wilmington 
this month at three health fairs organized by medical students and residents. 
</P>
<P>
 The testing is a project of the Department of Family Medicine at Harbor/UCLA 
Medical Center near Torrance, which offered vaccinations in Wilmington last 
year. 
</P>
<P>
 Free lead screenings for children are being added because many area homes are 
older and may have been painted with lead-based paint.  
</P>
<P>
 Lead screenings, vaccinations and physical examinations are free for children 
ages 6 and under, and free tetanus vaccines are available for adults. 
</P>
<P>
 The health fairs will be held 1 to 7 p.m. Saturday at the Wilmington Fiesta in 
Banning Park; 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. July 24 at the Holy Family Church, 1122 E. 
Robidoux St., and 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. July 30 at the Dana Strand Community 
Center. 
</P>
<P>
 More information is available from the Wilmington Vaccination and Lead 
Screening Project, 508 East E St., Wilmington, (310) 830-3401, 830-4254 or 
830-4629. 
</P>
</TEXT>
