<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: ARCADIA; TWO GIRLS, 16, ESCAPE KIDNAPING ATTEMPT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Arcadia police are searching for a man who shot two teen-age girls with a stun 
gun and tried to kidnap them as they walked home in a quiet residential 
neighborhood. 
</P>
<P>
 Police describe the suspect as an African American man between the ages of 30 
and 35; he is 6 feet, 3 inches tall, weighs more than over 200 pounds and has a 
shaved head.He was wearing what appeared to be a red nylon warm-up suit at the 
time of the incident, police said. The two 16-year-old girls were attacked 
about 10:30 p.m. July 5 while walking in the 1300 block of Golden West Avenue, 
which borders Temple City, Arcadia Police Capt. Dave Hinig said.  
</P>
<P>
 They were approached from behind by a man who grabbed one of them by the neck 
and tried to pull her into a maroon 1990 or 1991 Dodge van. He discharged the 
stun gun at her back, Hinig said, as the teen-ager resisted and screamed. He 
then grabbed the other girl and shot her with the stun gun in the upper torso. 
</P>
<P>
 A 29-year-old Temple City man heard the girls' screams, Hinig said and ran to 
their aid. The suspect jumped into the van and fled. 
</P>
<P>
 The girls' injuries were superficial, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
