<TEXT>
<P>
 BALDWIN PARK: A 14-year-old Baldwin Park boy was arrested Monday in El Monte 
after he allegedly used a gun to steal a car and other property two days 
earlier in Baldwin Park. The youth, whose name was not released, had allegedly 
stolen a car, a wallet and a pager from Jose Luis Alcala, a 23-year-old West 
Covina resident who was washing his car at a coin-operated carwash when the 
incident occurred at 3:10 a.m. Saturday. The suspect was spotted in the car at 
about 1 a.m. Monday in the 2500 block of Parkway Drive in El Monte, police 
said. They are searching for a second suspect. 
</P>
<P>
 LA PUENTE: A 2-year-old La Puente boy was killed Monday morning when his 
mother's car was broadsided by another car. The toddler, Adrian Cardenas, was 
wearing a seat belt but was not in a baby car seat as required by state law 
when the car he was riding in was struck at Amar Road and Valinda Avenue. The 
mother, Dorothy Cardenas, and two other children in the car, a 4-year-old boy 
and a 1-year-old girl, sustained minor injuries, California Highway Patrol 
officers said. Cardenas was headed eastbound on Amar and was making a left turn 
at Valinda when she was hit by a station wagon driven by Ismael Gonzales Frias, 
21, of West Covina. CHP officers are trying to determine who was at fault and 
are looking for witnesses to the 10:25 a.m. accident. Frias sustained minor 
injuries. Anyone with information may the CHP at (818) 338-1164. 
</P>
<P>
 POMONA: A 2-year-old Pomona boy drowned Monday evening in the family swimming 
pool. The body of Luis Martinez was found in the pool in the 600 block of 
Hobson Street at about 6:30 p.m., police said. He apparently had entered the 
back yard through an unlocked gate, police said.  
</P>
<P>
 WEST COVINA: A Wells Fargo bank was robbed of about $500 Saturday morning. The 
bank at 1540 West Covina Parkway was robbed at 10:45 a.m. by a man in his 
mid-30s who told a teller he had a gun and told her to hand over all of the 
money in her drawer. He then walked out the front door and, according to 
witnesses, got into an older model white station wagon, police said. 
</P>
