<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEMORIAL: PASADENA'S DAY OF THE AFRICAN CHILD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mayor Katie Nack proclaimed June 16, "The Day of the African Child" in 
Pasadena.The pronouncement says Pasadena will be "remembering the children of 
Soweto, South Africa, who were massacred in 1976 while speaking out against the 
injustice of apartheid." 
</P>
<P>
 Shockingly, nowhere to be found in the proclamation is any mention of the 
African children slaughtered in Rwanda, starved in Ethiopia and Sudan or 
massacred in Somalia and Uganda during recent years. 
</P>
<P>
 I thought the moral bankruptcy of such politically selective compassion had 
been left behind with our previous mayor, Rick Cole. But apparently I am wrong. 
</P>
<P>
 GLEN J. KISSEL 
</P>
<P>
 Pasadena  
</P>
