<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOTEBOOK / GARY KLEIN; STANDOUT RANCHO VERDE GUARD WILL ATTEND AZUSA PACIFIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GARY KLEIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Beverly Hunt, a 5-foot-7 guard from Rancho Verde High in Moreno Valley, has 
signed a letter of intent to play basketball next season at Azusa Pacific 
University. 
</P>
<P>
 Hunt averaged 15 points and 10 rebounds as a senior. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Jack Hwang, a recent graduate of Arcadia High, was one of 24 student athletes 
nationally who will receive $1,500 scholarships through Footaction USA's 
"Hooked on Sports Not Drugs or Violence" program. 
</P>
<P>
 Hwang was selected based on his academic achievement, financial need, and an 
essay about how sports and academics positively influenced his life. 
</P>
<P>
 The city of La Verne is accepting registration for a Southern California 
Municipal Athletic Federation C/D slow-pitch softball tournament that will be 
played July 23. 
</P>
<P>
 All SCMAF-sanctioned teams are eligible. Information: (909) 596-8700. 
</P>
<P>
 Registration is also open for a co-ed tournament that will be played Aug. 6. 
Information: (818) 448-0853. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Foothill-Citrus Officials Assn. is seeking people interested in becoming 
football officials for the upcoming high school season. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials must be available to work games played Thursdays and Fridays at 3:15 
p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The group will have its first meeting Aug. 23 at West Covina High. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (818) 964-9445. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 A golf tournament that will benefit the Hacienda Heights Library will be 
staged Aug. 22 at Hacienda Golf Club in La Habra Heights. 
</P>
<P>
 A $200 donation includes a golf cart, lunch on the course, dinner and an 
auction. Proceeds will be used to purchase materials for the children's 
collection of the library. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (818) 968-9357. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 A slow-pitch softball league for players 50 and older is being organized by 
the West Covina Senior Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Games will be played Wednesday evenings and there is no fee for participation. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (818) 331-5366. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 A men's soccer league is being formed in South El Monte for beginning and 
novice players. 
</P>
<P>
 Skills instruction and game coaching will be offered. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (818) 575-0114. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Registration is open for the La Verne University basketball camp, which is 
open to boys and girls in grades four through 11. 
</P>
<P>
 Session dates are July 25-29 and Aug. 1-5. Information: (909) 593-3511, Ext. 
4269. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 La Salle High is sponsoring summer boys and girls camps. 
</P>
<P>
 The basketball camp is for youths ages 8 through 13 and is scheduled for July 
25-29. Information: (818) 705-6733. 
</P>
<P>
 The softball camp is open to players ages 7 to 15. Information: (818) 
351-8951. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Arcadia Recreation Department has begun registration for a men's 
slow-pitch softball league that will begin play July 26. 
</P>
<P>
 Games are played Mondays and Wednesdays or Tuesdays and Thursday evenings at 
Bonita Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (818) 574-5113. 
</P>
