CLINTON PICKS CHILE ENVOY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The White House has announced that President Clinton intends to nominate 
Gabriel Guerra-Mondragon to be ambassador to Chile. He previously served in the 
Foreign Service and was a staff attorney for the Civil Rights Commission. 
</P>
