METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: INGLEWOOD; L.A. SUES 
INGLEWOOD, FIRM OVER OIL DRILLING PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city of Los Angeles has filed suit against Inglewood and an oil drilling 
company over a proposed drilling project at the Inglewood Park Cemetery. 
</P>
<P>
 The suit alleges that Inglewood violated the California Environmental Quality 
Act by granting Vortex Energy and Minerals Ltd. a permit to drill for oil on 
what is now empty land without completing an environmental impact report. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles Councilwoman Ruth Galanter, whose district borders the Inglewood 
site, said she is concerned about traffic the project will create, and other 
impacts such as ground water contamination and possible earthquakes. The 
drilling site is next to an offshoot of the Newport -- Inglewood fault. 
</P>
<P>
 Inglewood officials acknowledge that they have not done a full environmental 
report, but say they are not violating the law because all relevant impacts 
have been addressed. 
</P>
