<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUSPECT ARRESTED AFTER CAR CHASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A suspected child molester was arrested Wednesday night after a 1 1/2-hour car 
chase that started near Downtown Los Angeles and ended on a freeway near 
Diamond Bar, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The pursuit began about 7:45 p.m., when police spotted a vehicle believed to 
be connected to a child molestation, said LAPD Officer Don Cox.. 
</P>
<P>
 Cox said police first ordered the gray Mazda pickup truck to pull over near 
Sunset Boulevard and Parkview Street.When the driver refused, a chase ensued, 
as the pickup -- staying well within the speed limit -- led half a dozen squad 
cars from the northbound Glendale Freeway to the southbound Orange Freeway, 
traveling on the Ventura, Foothill and Golden State freeways.  
</P>
<P>
 About 9 p.m., the truck stopped on the southbound Orange Freeway. Surrounded 
by squad cars, the suspect surrendered without incident. 
</P>
