<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; GARAGE SALE TO HELP FORM BUSINESS WATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After years of criticizing ill-kept businesses for luring criminals to their 
neighborhoods, a group of Van Nuys residents will each take a little something 
from their own homes to keep crime away from local merchants. 
</P>
<P>
 A garage sale by a coalition of Neighborhood Watch groups called the Guardian 
Eyes of Van Nuys is expected to raise funds to create a new Business Watch in 
the city's leading area for reported rapes.The sale will be held from 8 a.m. to 
6 p.m. Saturday and Sunday at 15242 Covello St., Van Nuys. 
</P>
<P>
 The sale will raise funds for the year-old Neighborhood Watch group and help 
pay start-up costs, including a newsletter, for the Business Watch proposed by 
Leslie Bashaar, a local real estate agent and activist for the Guardian Eyes, 
which represents about 1,200 homeowners. 
</P>
<P>
 Bashaar said the new Business Watch would be located between Saticoy and 
Raymer streets and Van Nuys and Sepulveda boulevards. JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
