<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: BURBANK; BOWMAN TO HEAD AIRPORT AUTHORITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HENRY CHU 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Longtime Commissioner Brian Bowman of Burbank has been named new president of 
the Burbank-Glendale-Pasadena Airport Authority, which oversees Burbank 
Airport. 
</P>
<P>
 Bowman, previously the authority's vice president, was elected unanimously by 
commissioners this week.He succeeds Robert W. Garcin of Glendale, who headed 
the panel for 10 years and remains a commissioner. 
</P>
<P>
 Replacing Bowman as vice president is Carl Raggio Jr. of Glendale. The new 
secretary is Joyce A. Streator of Pasadena, a new commissioner and the only 
woman on the nine-member body. 
</P>
<P>
 Bowman's term as president will last one year. An executive with a plumbing 
supply company, he has served on the commission since 1986, representing the 
city of Burbank. Each of the three cities that oversee the airport appoints 
three commissioners, who serve four-year terms. HENRY CHU 
</P>
</TEXT>
