SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; MAN STEALS $5,000 FROM AREA BANK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man stole about $5,000 from a bank Wednesday afternoon after showing the 
butt of a handgun to a bank teller, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The robbery occurred at about 3:10 p.m. at the Wells Fargo Bank at 19310 
Soledad Canyon Road, said Sgt. Richard Lichten of the Santa Clarita Valley 
Sheriff's Station.He said the suspect remains at large. 
</P>
<P>
 The man walked into the bank, held up a white bag and demanded cash from a 
teller, according to a sheriff's report. He then displayed what appeared to be 
a blue steel handgun of unknown caliber in his waistband. 
</P>
<P>
 He drove away from the bank in a black Volkswagen Jetta and was last seen 
driving south over the Whites Canyon Road bridge behind the bank, Lichten said. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspect may be the same man who committed a similar robbery at the bank 
about a month ago, according to sheriff's officials. But they emphasized that 
further investigation is needed. 
