<P>
 Foothill High School will have two new assistant principals when the 1994-95 
school year begins in September. 
</P>
<P>
 Joining the school are Brooke Harms-Vogelgesang, an assistant principal at 
Tustin High School for the last two years, and Anthony Kuns, an administrator 
from Chino Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
 They will replace Dawn Clemens, who is moving out of the district, and Charles 
Milligan, newly appointed principal of Spring View Middle School in Huntington 
Beach. 
</P>
