which also has a new principal, Bob Boies, former principal at Columbus Tustin 
Middle School. 
</P>
<P>
 Columbus Tustin Middle School, which moved to Browning Avenue while the Beneta 
Way site was renovated, will return to its original site in September under a 
new principal, Adele Casso Heuer, a former administrator in the ABC Unified 
School District in Los Angeles County. 
</P>
<P>
 Heuer will have Pat James as assistant principal. James has been principal at 
Robert P. Heideman Elementary School for seven years. He will be replaced there 
by Louise Saladino, who came from the Orange Unified School District. BERT 
ELJERA 
