<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA BEACH; NUDE MAN ARRESTED AFTER TRAFFIC CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A nude, 23-year-old man was arrested here Wednesday after crashing his pickup 
truck into two vehicles, then ricocheting off three others, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Phillip Harvey Kile of Seal Beach was taken into custody about 10:10 a.m. in a 
hilly area in the 20200 block of Laguna Canyon Road after running from his 
wrecked 1988 Chevrolet pickup truck, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Kile was taken to Saddleback Memorial Medical Center, then transported to the 
Orange County Jail, where he was being held on suspicion of driving under the 
influence, reckless driving, hit-and-run driving and driving on a suspended 
license, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 A California Highway Patrol officer noticed Kile's truck traveling erratically 
northbound on El Toro Road near Moulton Parkway, according to authorities. 
</P>
<P>
 The officer turned on his overhead lights and gave chase, but broke off when 
the truck speeded up and the officer believed it was too dangerous to continue, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 As the CHP officer was sending in a report over his radio, he reached the 
accident scene. 
</P>
<P>
 Kile's truck hit two vehicles as he drove in the oncoming southbound lane of 
Laguna Canyon Road, then struck three more vehicles waiting at a traffic 
signal, police said. When arrested, Kile was hiding face down amid weeds and 
rocks, they said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police Sgt. Ray Lardie said there were no serious injuries. Police had no 
explanation why Kile was naked. JEFF BEAN 
</P>
