HOUSTON GRAND JURY CLEARS USC RECRUIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A grand jury in Houston found insufficient evidence to indict USC football 
recruit Antoine Simpson on sexual assault charges, according to Kent Schaffer, 
Simpson's attorney. 
</P>
<P>
 Simpson and a friend had been accused by a teen-ager in Houston of assaulting 
her at a party May 29. 
</P>
<P>
 Schaffer said Simpson, a defensive lineman, still intends to enroll at USC 
this fall. 
</P>
