<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94: SEMIFINALS; FOLLOWING THEIR LEADERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 There would be no surprises in Wednesday's semifinals, no unknowns stealing 
the thunder. Brazil's Romario and Italy's Roberto Baggio, two of the biggest 
names in the world of soccer, were front and center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA071494-0272 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 060543 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
July 14, 1994, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
