ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: DENSE-PAC GETS $400,000 ORDER FROM OVERSEAS FOR 
PROTOTYPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dense-Pac Microsystems Inc., which makes computer memory devices and 
semiconductors for military and industrial use, said Wednesday that an 
international company has ordered a $400,000 prototype of products to be used 
in aircraft tracking systems. 
</P>
<P>
 Dense-Pac, based in Garden Grove, did not reveal the name of the purchaser. 
The devices will be delivered over the next six months, the company said. 
