<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: QLOGIC CORP. REPORTS PROFITS INCREASED 48% IN 1ST 
QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 QLogic Corp., a Costa Mesa computer products company, reported earnings of 
$534,000 for its latest quarter.That was up 48% from a profit of $362,000 for 
the same period a year earlier. Revenue for the company's first fiscal quarter, 
which ended July 3, was $14.2 million, up 9% from $13.0 million for the same 
period a year earlier. QLogic became an independent, publicly traded company 
when its shares were distributed to stockholders of record of Emulex Corp. on 
Feb. 28. 
</P>
