<P>
TWO INMATES DIE DURING MELEE INSIDE CONNECTICUT PRISON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Club-wielding inmates wearing makeshift hoods attacked other inmates during a 
prison yard melee that left two prisoners dead and at least six others injured, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Two of the injured were in critical condition Wednesday. Two guards also 
suffered minor injuries during the fighting Tuesday in the recreation area of 
the medium-security Carl Robinson Correctional Institution. 
</P>
<P>
 About 200 of the prison's 1,600 inmates were in the yard when some prisoners 
apparently fashioned hoods from their T-shirts and chased down others with 
sticks and makeshift clubs. One inmate was swinging a crutch. 
</P>
<P>
 State corrections spokesman Bill Flower said officials did not know what 
caused the fight. 
</P>
