<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Wrong information -- An article and an accompanying headline in Wednesday's 
edition incorrectly reported that officials of the Moorpark Boys & Girls Club 
told a Moorpark City Council committee that the club has debts of 
$55,000.According to Antoinette I. Carbone-Sarcinella, the club's executive 
director, the club does not have a projected deficit of $25,000, as reported. 
Instead, she said, there is only a possible shortfall of $2,600 this fiscal 
year. The club also owes $30,000 in back taxes, she said, but is working to pay 
that back. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Correction 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA071494-0397 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 060668 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
July 14, 1994, Thursday, Southland Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 4; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
