<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL JOURNAL: LONG BEACH; OFFICIALS NAME MANAGER FOR QUEENSWAY PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Robert Paternoster, director of planning and building, will manage the 
$557-million plan to remake the city's waterfront, city officials announced. 
</P>
<P>
 Paternoster has overseen preparation of the massive project, known as the 
Queensway Bay Plan, since its conception two years ago.As project manager, he 
will be responsible for coordinating the financing, construction, marketing, 
permits and other aspects. 
</P>
<P>
 The proposal calls for a redevelopment of 310 acres of downtown waterfront 
land, mostly on an old landfill where the Shoreline Aquatic Park and lagoon are 
located. The lagoon would be dredged to accommodate ships, and the new harbor 
would be surrounded with shops, restaurants, hotels and an aquarium. 
</P>
<P>
 City Manager James C. Hankla appointed Eugene Zeller, superintendent of 
building and safety, to be acting director of planning and building in 
Paternoster's absence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
