<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: CERRITOS; SPEED LIMIT REDUCED ON BLOOMFIELD AVENUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The speed limit on a stretch of Bloomfield Avenue from 166th Street to Alondra 
Boulevard will be reduced to 40 m.p.h. from 45 m.p.h. on Aug. 7 in response to 
residents' complaints that fast-moving trucks are making too much noise as they 
rumble through the neighborhood.  
</P>
<P>
 The stretch is a truck route that bisects the city's industrial area, making 
it a busy thoroughfare for vehicles traveling toward Santa Fe Springs, said 
Public Works Director Vince Brar. The speed limit is 40 m.p.h. along the rest 
of Bloomfield in the city, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
